# Capture screenshots are large and churn on every UI change (re-rendered byte-for-byte
# even when unchanged), so they're NOT tracked — they're regenerable with `pnpm i18n:shots`.
# What IS tracked: `capture-report.json` (the surface→keys coupling source + freshness-check
# input) and the `@key.screenshot` refs in the `en/*.json` catalogs. Screenshots are an
# optional translator aid (the `@key` descriptions are the primary one), so a checkout without
# them degrades gracefully — see docs/guides/i18n.md § Screenshots.
*.png

# Transient per-run failure list (should be empty in a good state; real failures
# surface in the run output + the failing test). The durable known-gaps record is
# `capture-skipped.json` (tracked) + the coverage report.
capture-failed.json
